         <div type="poem"
              xml:id="txt_GrayTh1716_skoc"
              corresp="authors.xml#txt_GrayTh1716_skoc"
              subtype="eceptext"
              rendition="#lgvspace"
              rhyme="aa"
              met="-+|--+|--+|---+/              -+|--+|--+|--+-/              -+|--+|--+|--+/              -+|--+|--+|--+/              -+|--+|--+|--+/              -+|--+|--+|--+/"
              n="12"
              ana="#tetrameter #couplet #anapaest #catalexis #hypercatalexis">
            <link type="author" target="authors.xml#aut_GrayTh1716"/>
            <head>[Sketch of his Own Character]</head>
            <lg>
               <l n="1">Too poor for a bribe and too proud to importune,</l>
               <l n="2">He had not the method of making a fortune:</l>
               <l n="3">Could love and could hate, so was thought somewhat odd;</l>
               <l n="4">No very great wit, he believed in a God.</l>
               <l n="5">A post or a pension he did not desire,</l>
               <l n="6">But left church and state to Charles Townshend and Squire.</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
